Note: Test Runner for Advanced Integration Tests
Process called "run_advanced_integration_tests" returns Boolean:
    Let integration_tests be list containing:
        test_hot_reload_with_macro_expansion
        test_jit_compilation_with_hot_reload
        test_memory_ownership_with_jit
        test_macro_system_with_memory_management
        test_advanced_modules_performance
        test_error_handling_integration
    
    Let passed_count be 0
    Let total_count be length of integration_tests
    
    Display "Running " plus total_count plus " advanced integration tests..."
    Display "======================================================="
    
    For each test in integration_tests:
        Let test_name be get_test_name with test as test
        Display "Running: " plus test_name
        
        Let test_start_time be get_current_time
        Let result be test
        Let test_end_time be get_current_time
        Let test_duration be test_end_time minus test_start_time
        
        If result:
            Display "✅ " plus test_name plus " PASSED (" plus test_duration plus "s)"
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Display "❌ " plus test_name plus " FAILED (" plus test_duration plus "s)"
    
    Display "======================================================="
    Display "Integration Test Results: " plus passed_count plus "/" plus total_count plus " tests passed"
    
    If passed_count is equal to total_count:
        Display "🎉 All advanced integration tests passed!"
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display "⚠️  Some advanced integration tests failed"
        Let success_rate be (passed_count divided by total_count) multiplied by 100
        Display "Success rate: " plus success_rate plus "%"
        Return false

Process called "get_test_name" that takes test as Process returns String:
    Note: Implementation would extract function name from process
    Return "integration_test"

Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Note: Implementation should return high-precision timestamp
    Return 1640995200.123456